      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I'm working on this module for our new kernel-level middleware. My boss is being a total pain about the dependency count—he says we have a strict limit for the final audit and basically any unnecessary external imports will get the whole PR rejected. We need to keep the dependency count as low as humanly possible to pass the review.\n\nHere is the current setup:\n- `cryptography` (for AES and SHA-256)\n- `requests` (for sending telemetry to our backend)\n- `pandas` (for processing local logs)\n- `numpy` (for some math ops in the telemetry)\n- `pyyaml` (for config parsing)\n\nCan you refactor this architecture to minimize the total number of unique external imports? The goal is to get that count down to the absolute minimum so we don't fail the audit.",
